===Etymology 1===
1775, from {{compound|en|hand|cuff|t2=end of shirtsleeve}}.<ref name="oetlyd">{{R:Online Etymology Dictionary}}</ref>

Possibly influenced by {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|handcops}}, from {{m|ang|hand}} + {{m|ang|cops||fetter, chains}}, but due to lack of continuity (centuries between Old English and modern term), generally analyzed as a re-invention.<ref name="oetlyd" />

====Noun====
{{en-plural noun}}

# {{lb|en|plurale tantum}} A [[fastening]] consisting of two [[metal]] [[ring]]s, designed to go around a person's [[wrist]]s, and connected by a [[chain]] or [[hinge]].
